WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.135 --> 00:00:06.300
<i>Carroll was convicted in 2004 for
the murders of 14 young women...</i>

2
00:00:06.473 --> 00:00:09.307
<i>We need you in Virginia. Ryan.</i>
RYAN: I'm not an agent anymore.

3
00:00:09.476 --> 00:00:12.116
<i>You caught Carroll. No
one knows him like you do.</i>

4
00:00:12.145 --> 00:00:15.547
- What's my sequel about. Joe? CARROLL:
We're going to write this together...

5
00:00:17.284 --> 00:00:19.276
even though you
slept with my wife.

6
00:00:19.820 --> 00:00:22.915
I have so many
surprises waiting for you.

7
00:00:24.291 --> 00:00:27.659
- Agent Parker's taking the lead.
- Cults. My specialty.

8
00:00:27.995 --> 00:00:29.195
We know about the cult...

9
00:00:29.396 --> 00:00:30.989
gay neighbors and the nanny.

10
00:00:31.164 --> 00:00:33.156
How do they figure
into your new plot?

11
00:00:33.667 --> 00:00:37.365
- Why is my dad such a bad man?
- Maybe he's not so bad.

12
00:00:37.538 --> 00:00:39.029
I need the phone. Where is it?

13
00:00:39.206 --> 00:00:41.937
They found a signal in upstate
New York. Dutchess County.

14
00:00:42.109 --> 00:00:44.101
- We're gonna find Joey.
- I know you will.

15
00:00:44.311 --> 00:00:47.042
- Guys. this is Megan.
- You were going to deal with this.

16
00:00:47.214 --> 00:00:49.454
Paul brought her here.
- Jacob's never killed.

17
00:00:49.616 --> 00:00:51.881
You should do it. Jacob.
Since you never have.

18
00:00:52.052 --> 00:00:53.179
Get out of here. go!

19
00:00:53.353 --> 00:00:54.548
She's getting away!

20
00:00:57.224 --> 00:00:58.749
We both love him. Paul.

21
00:00:59.560 --> 00:01:01.324
Emma? I'm sorry.

22
00:01:02.429 --> 00:01:03.727
We're not giving up on you.

23
00:01:38.665 --> 00:01:40.395
You okay?

24
00:01:41.068 --> 00:01:43.435
- Where are you going?
- Bathroom.

25
00:01:43.604 --> 00:01:44.765
Are you freaking out?

26
00:01:45.572 --> 00:01:48.804
No. I'm fine. I
just have to pee.

27
00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:15.697
Jacob's freaking out. isn't he?

28
00:02:16.536 --> 00:02:18.698
Well. he wasn't last night.

29
00:02:22.709 --> 00:02:23.836
That was fun.

30
00:02:24.011 --> 00:02:26.207
Off the charts.

31
00:02:53.073 --> 00:02:54.939
I'm hungry.

32
00:02:55.976 --> 00:02:57.740
You hungry?

33
00:02:58.078 --> 00:03:00.138
Starved.

34
00:03:02.983 --> 00:03:04.576
All right.

35
00:03:16.763 --> 00:03:19.358
Hello. JOEY: <i>Mom?</i>

36
00:03:20.567 --> 00:03:21.694
Joey?

37
00:03:21.868 --> 00:03:23.928
Honey? Where are you?

38
00:03:24.104 --> 00:03:25.868
I wanna go home.
Why can't I come home?

39
00:03:26.039 --> 00:03:29.100
Um. just tell me where
you are. I'll come get you.

40
00:03:29.276 --> 00:03:30.574
<i>Somewhere in the country.</i>

41
00:03:30.744 --> 00:03:32.736
Why'd you make
Denise bring me here?

42
00:03:32.913 --> 00:03:34.779
Where in the country are you?

43
00:03:34.981 --> 00:03:38.110
I don't know.
it's a big house...

44
00:03:38.618 --> 00:03:40.849
<i>- like a farm.</i>
- Keep him talking.

45
00:03:41.021 --> 00:03:42.887
What color is the house. Joey?

46
00:03:43.056 --> 00:03:46.390
It's white with
black shutters...

47
00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:48.722
and it's really big.
with an upstairs.

48
00:03:48.895 --> 00:03:52.263
And it's far from the street and
they won't let me leave the yard.

49
00:03:55.736 --> 00:03:57.705
Is Denise still
with you right now?

50
00:03:57.871 --> 00:04:00.033
Yeah. And Paul and Jacob.

51
00:04:00.207 --> 00:04:01.903
<i>I don't really like Paul.</i>

52
00:04:02.075 --> 00:04:04.135
Why? Why. baby? Did he hurt you?

53
00:04:04.311 --> 00:04:05.370
No. but he's mean.

54
00:04:07.147 --> 00:04:08.809
Do they know
you're talking to me?

55
00:04:09.015 --> 00:04:12.281
No way. They'd kill me if
they knew I was on the phone.

56
00:04:12.452 --> 00:04:15.286
You don't have to worry
because I'm gonna come get you.

57
00:04:15.455 --> 00:04:17.219
<i>Okay. Tell Denise
to bring me home.</i>

58
00:04:17.390 --> 00:04:19.416
- Okay? Aah! PAUL: What
the hell are you doing?

59
00:04:19.593 --> 00:04:22.495
Joey? Joey?

60
00:04:25.031 --> 00:04:27.091
Joey!

61
00:04:27.267 --> 00:04:28.792
Joey!

62
00:04:38.178 --> 00:04:39.476
Mike. what do you got?

63
00:04:39.646 --> 00:04:42.810
Cell phone Joey used was scrambled
with an algorithm. like Maggie Schuller's.

64
00:04:42.983 --> 00:04:44.781
- You worked past it.
- Not exactly.

65
00:04:44.951 --> 00:04:49.150
Joey hung up. the phone switched to wi-fi.
pinged a signal in Baton Rouge. Louisiana.

66
00:04:49.322 --> 00:04:50.517
You said Dutchess County.

67
00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:54.252
It was. Opening the files triggered
a virus. I can't be sure of anything.

68
00:04:54.861 --> 00:04:57.660
Hey. isn't that Joe
Carroll's attorney?

69
00:04:57.831 --> 00:05:00.164
Thought he represented himself.
- At trial.

70
00:05:00.333 --> 00:05:02.996
Olivia Warren handled his
appeals. What's she doing here?

71
00:05:03.670 --> 00:05:06.196
Oh. no. We gotta shut
this down. Send her away.

72
00:05:06.439 --> 00:05:08.533
No reason she needs
to meet with Joe today.

73
00:05:08.708 --> 00:05:11.769
We can't. He has a right
to speak to his attorney.

74
00:05:11.945 --> 00:05:14.323
He knows we're close to finding
Joey. he's planning something.

75
00:05:14.347 --> 00:05:18.284
- We've got to get to Dutchess County now.
- Not until we confirm the location.

76
00:05:20.787 --> 00:05:22.187
Gonna take a couple hours...

77
00:05:22.355 --> 00:05:24.221
- to work through this mess.
- Hurry.

78
00:05:24.391 --> 00:05:26.883
Whatever you have
to do. Mike. just hurry.

79
00:05:28.295 --> 00:05:29.820
Why can't I go home?

80
00:05:30.030 --> 00:05:31.692
Mom said she was
gonna come get me.

81
00:05:32.132 --> 00:05:34.192
Honey. I told you.

82
00:05:34.367 --> 00:05:36.632
Your mom's worried that
you might be in danger.

83
00:05:36.803 --> 00:05:41.298
She acted like she didn't know where I
was. She was scared and asking questions.

84
00:05:41.474 --> 00:05:43.170
There are things you don't know.

85
00:05:43.343 --> 00:05:46.871
Like what? I know about my
dad. I know he's a bad man.

86
00:05:48.381 --> 00:05:51.010
What if I told you that
your dad wasn't a bad man?

87
00:05:51.618 --> 00:05:54.884
Then why was he in prison? And
why are the police looking for him?

88
00:05:55.055 --> 00:05:59.117
It's complicated. Joey. and
really hard to understand.

89
00:05:59.426 --> 00:06:01.986
But the police are the bad men.

90
00:06:02.162 --> 00:06:04.893
- Policemen are good.
- Not always.

91
00:06:05.632 --> 00:06:07.828
They are lying about your dad.

92
00:06:08.001 --> 00:06:10.197
That's why your
mom sent us here.

93
00:06:10.370 --> 00:06:15.536
To hide from them. To make
sure nothing happens to you.

94
00:06:22.182 --> 00:06:23.582
Hey.

95
00:06:23.750 --> 00:06:26.777
Hey. cupcake. Gonna wake up?

96
00:06:26.953 --> 00:06:28.046
Wake up.

97
00:06:36.196 --> 00:06:37.926
That's not so bad.

98
00:06:42.068 --> 00:06:43.866
Please.

99
00:06:44.037 --> 00:06:46.336
I wanna go home.

100
00:06:47.707 --> 00:06:50.438
You're not going home. Megan.

101
00:06:51.544 --> 00:06:52.773
Never again.

102
00:06:54.781 --> 00:06:58.616
I think we've established that. A
little acceptance might go a long way.

103
00:07:05.558 --> 00:07:08.289
It won't be long now.

104
00:07:08.895 --> 00:07:10.693
I promise.

105
00:07:24.844 --> 00:07:27.143
Hey. where's Emma?

106
00:07:28.014 --> 00:07:30.574
- She's upstairs talking to Joey.
- Hmm.

107
00:07:33.153 --> 00:07:36.214
Well. it was an untraceable
satellite phone. so we're safe.

108
00:07:36.790 --> 00:07:38.816
What if he told his
mom where we are?

109
00:07:38.992 --> 00:07:42.485
He has no idea where he is. I've
been thinking about little Megan.

110
00:07:44.130 --> 00:07:47.589
I don't think you should go with
the big blade. It is your first time...

111
00:07:47.767 --> 00:07:51.602
and it's likely for your
stabs to be tentative.

112
00:07:52.739 --> 00:07:55.868
I think it's better for you to go
with something thin and sharp...

113
00:07:56.042 --> 00:07:58.944
like this. Has more impact.

114
00:07:59.679 --> 00:08:01.648
All right. you can do this.

115
00:08:01.982 --> 00:08:03.041
I know you can.

116
00:08:05.986 --> 00:08:07.045
What's your problem?

117
00:08:07.253 --> 00:08:09.813
I'm not gay. all right?

118
00:08:11.191 --> 00:08:12.284
Last night was great.

119
00:08:13.193 --> 00:08:14.286
No. it wasn't.

120
00:08:15.996 --> 00:08:17.862
- You could have fooled me.
- Look...

121
00:08:20.300 --> 00:08:24.203
I can't be what you
want me to be. Paul.

122
00:08:24.904 --> 00:08:26.031
I can't.

123
00:08:26.573 --> 00:08:29.042
It's just not who I am.

124
00:08:31.778 --> 00:08:34.839
Why do you always
have to label everything?

125
00:08:35.048 --> 00:08:37.415
Last night was exactly
what it was supposed to be.

126
00:08:38.151 --> 00:08:41.485
For the first time. you. me
and Emma were really together.

127
00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:43.919
No lies. no secrets.

128
00:08:44.090 --> 00:08:45.991
It felt right.

129
00:08:47.861 --> 00:08:50.330
There's only one
thing missing now.

130
00:08:57.103 --> 00:08:59.368
Will you just do it for me?

131
00:09:02.342 --> 00:09:03.867
No more lies. Jacob.

132
00:09:05.378 --> 00:09:07.847
This is about trust now.

133
00:09:09.315 --> 00:09:13.252
Emma and I believe
in you. You can do this.

134
00:09:32.138 --> 00:09:35.575
Olivia. Come on in.

135
00:09:44.117 --> 00:09:46.382
Oh. please. Do sit down.

136
00:09:57.297 --> 00:09:59.061
Why am I here?

137
00:09:59.232 --> 00:10:02.862
I require legal counsel.
My first thought was of you.

138
00:10:04.304 --> 00:10:06.466
There's nothing I can
do for you. Mr. Carroll.

139
00:10:06.639 --> 00:10:08.631
Legally or otherwise.

140
00:10:10.577 --> 00:10:14.878
Now. we both
know that isn't true.

141
00:10:15.815 --> 00:10:18.375
You owe me a few favors.

142
00:10:18.751 --> 00:10:20.743
<i>I'm sorry we lost the appeal.</i>

143
00:10:20.920 --> 00:10:22.183
Then file another one.

144
00:10:22.388 --> 00:10:26.484
I think it's time you considered
another firm. Mr. Carroll.

145
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:28.193
Perhaps the ACLU...

146
00:10:28.795 --> 00:10:32.323
You've garnered a great deal of
attention while representing me.

147
00:10:32.899 --> 00:10:35.459
It's helped your career.

148
00:10:36.002 --> 00:10:38.335
I want you. Olivia.

149
00:10:39.339 --> 00:10:43.299
There's nothing more for us
to gain. Mr. Carroll. I am sorry.

150
00:10:44.777 --> 00:10:46.905
Goodbye and good luck.

151
00:10:58.858 --> 00:11:04.161
Ryan Hardy has more than
surprised with his get-up-and-go.

152
00:11:04.330 --> 00:11:07.960
So I need to move things
along slightly faster...

153
00:11:08.134 --> 00:11:09.932
than I had originally planned.

154
00:11:10.837 --> 00:11:12.135
I don't follow.

155
00:11:12.305 --> 00:11:16.367
I need to know everything
that's happening behind that door.

156
00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:19.673
Both in the media
and within the FBI.

157
00:11:19.846 --> 00:11:22.975
You still have your contacts?

158
00:11:26.519 --> 00:11:28.147
Yes?

159
00:11:29.722 --> 00:11:31.588
- Yes.
- Good.

160
00:11:31.758 --> 00:11:33.886
Then let's get started.

161
00:11:34.827 --> 00:11:39.026
You are about to have
a very busy day. Olivia.

162
00:11:54.581 --> 00:11:58.484
<i>Good morning. My
name is Olivia Warren.</i>

163
00:11:58.785 --> 00:12:01.778
<i>I have been retained
to represent Joe Carroll.</i>

164
00:12:01.988 --> 00:12:04.548
- What's going on?
- Joe Carroll press conference.

165
00:12:04.724 --> 00:12:07.558
- Told you he's up to something.
- In light of speculation...

166
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:10.219
about an alleged cult
following of Mr. Carroll...

167
00:12:10.396 --> 00:12:13.924
he has asked me to read
the following statement:

168
00:12:14.701 --> 00:12:17.762
<i>"He had come like a thief in
the night. And one by one...</i>

169
00:12:17.937 --> 00:12:21.931
<i>dropped the revelers in the
blood-bedewed halls of their revel...</i>

170
00:12:22.108 --> 00:12:25.704
<i>and died each in the
despairing posture of his fall."</i>

171
00:12:25.878 --> 00:12:28.905
- It's Poe.
- "The Masque of the Red Death."

172
00:12:29.082 --> 00:12:32.814
<i>"And the life of the ebony clock
went out with that of the last of the gay.</i>

173
00:12:33.019 --> 00:12:35.648
And the flames of
the tripods expired.

174
00:12:35.822 --> 00:12:39.884
<i>And Darkness and
Decay and the Red Death...</i>

175
00:12:40.059 --> 00:12:43.928
<i>held illimitable
dominion over all."</i>

176
00:12:48.401 --> 00:12:49.425
Hello.

177
00:12:49.969 --> 00:12:51.267
It's time.

178
00:12:55.975 --> 00:12:59.036
<i>That concludes Mr. Carroll's
statement. Thank you for coming.</i>

179
00:13:05.018 --> 00:13:08.648
- The Poe story...
- It's a mysterious stranger...

180
00:13:08.821 --> 00:13:11.586
moving from room to room.
killing people like a plague.

181
00:13:11.758 --> 00:13:14.990
Carroll's behind bars. A cult
needs to hear from its leader.

182
00:13:15.161 --> 00:13:17.960
A directive couched in
poetic verse makes it special.

183
00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:21.295
- Encoded message. Triggering someone.
- Narrowing down a location.

184
00:13:21.467 --> 00:13:23.479
You got it right the first
time. it's Dutchess County.

185
00:13:23.503 --> 00:13:26.268
They're scrambling you
with this virus. We gotta move.

186
00:13:28.675 --> 00:13:31.338
A helicopter will take you
to the nearest landing strip.

187
00:13:31.511 --> 00:13:34.845
Local P.D. will assist. Albany
field office is on standby.

188
00:13:35.315 --> 00:13:38.615
You will stay in contact
with me at all times.

189
00:13:38.785 --> 00:13:40.117
You understand?

190
00:13:40.520 --> 00:13:43.149
Agent Weston. that
was for your benefit.

191
00:13:43.856 --> 00:13:45.154
Yes. ma'am.

192
00:13:50.296 --> 00:13:51.889
Sign here.

193
00:13:53.966 --> 00:13:58.461
Do you solemnly swear
to uphold the Constitution...

194
00:13:59.038 --> 00:14:00.165
et cetera. et cetera?

195
00:14:00.340 --> 00:14:01.831
I do. PARKER: Good.

196
00:14:02.008 --> 00:14:03.670
You're deputized.

197
00:14:12.051 --> 00:14:14.350
How will you find him
without a specific location?

198
00:14:14.520 --> 00:14:16.716
We know the county.
description of the house.

199
00:14:16.889 --> 00:14:19.358
Gonna use local cops. Go
door to door if necessary.

200
00:14:19.525 --> 00:14:21.858
- I wanna go with you.
- It's better that you stay.

201
00:14:22.028 --> 00:14:24.657
In case Joey tries
to contact you again.

202
00:14:24.831 --> 00:14:28.063
Chopper's ready. We need to go.

203
00:14:43.750 --> 00:14:48.279
I know. the way I left things
with us. all those years ago...

204
00:14:48.454 --> 00:14:50.753
- I wasn't fair to you.
- Ryan. it's okay.

205
00:14:50.923 --> 00:14:53.620
There's so much I want to
say. I know now isn't the time.

206
00:14:53.793 --> 00:14:56.160
I really need to
bring Joey home.

207
00:14:57.296 --> 00:14:58.696
And then I want us to talk.

208
00:15:00.466 --> 00:15:02.025
Just be careful.

209
00:15:12.278 --> 00:15:14.076
Maybe Jacob's right.

210
00:15:14.247 --> 00:15:15.647
It's time to call Roderick.

211
00:15:15.815 --> 00:15:18.410
I already called
Roderick. Left a message.

212
00:15:19.051 --> 00:15:21.486
- He'll tell us what to do.
- What's up with the kid?

213
00:15:22.255 --> 00:15:23.951
I handled it like I always do.

214
00:15:24.123 --> 00:15:26.490
With a hug? That
kid needs a smacking.

215
00:15:26.692 --> 00:15:28.593
Don't even think about it.

216
00:15:29.095 --> 00:15:30.757
He's a kid. He wants his mother.

217
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:34.731
He's not dumb. He's gonna
know we're lying to him eventually.

218
00:15:34.967 --> 00:15:36.902
Joey's fine.

219
00:15:37.203 --> 00:15:38.262
How's Jacob?

220
00:15:38.771 --> 00:15:39.966
He's still down there.

221
00:15:41.107 --> 00:15:42.336
I'm giving him some time.

222
00:15:43.743 --> 00:15:45.405
And a little space.

223
00:15:54.520 --> 00:15:55.783
Are you in charge?

224
00:15:55.955 --> 00:15:59.119
- I'm Olivia Warren. I represent...
- I know who you are.

225
00:15:59.292 --> 00:16:01.852
I need to speak to
Claire Matthews. Alone.

226
00:16:02.028 --> 00:16:03.189
What do you want?

227
00:16:03.362 --> 00:16:06.093
You'll be very interested
in what I have to say.

228
00:16:10.269 --> 00:16:13.262
I saw your press conference.
What was that about?

229
00:16:13.439 --> 00:16:14.998
That's not why I'm here.

230
00:16:15.174 --> 00:16:17.871
But Joe did ask me
to deliver a message.

231
00:16:19.645 --> 00:16:21.238
If you want to see Joey...

232
00:16:21.447 --> 00:16:25.111
be at the corner of Broad and
26th Street at 3 p.m. this afternoon.

233
00:16:25.751 --> 00:16:27.879
Come alone. And tell no one.

234
00:16:28.054 --> 00:16:29.716
I don't understand.
The FBI said...

235
00:16:29.889 --> 00:16:32.381
Whatever the FBI has
told you is incorrect.

236
00:16:32.558 --> 00:16:36.962
According to your ex-husband.
the only way you'll see your son...

237
00:16:37.129 --> 00:16:39.155
is if you follow
these instructions.

238
00:16:40.333 --> 00:16:41.460
It's your decision.

239
00:17:05.191 --> 00:17:07.524
Hey! Let's take that one.

240
00:17:14.267 --> 00:17:17.101
<i>The county is 82</i> 5
<i>square miles total...</i>

241
00:17:17.303 --> 00:17:19.602
but we believe Joey's
call came from this cluster.

242
00:17:19.805 --> 00:17:22.036
Those cell towers serve
nearly half the county.

243
00:17:22.208 --> 00:17:26.111
We're looking for a two-story white
farmhouse. set back from the road.

244
00:17:26.312 --> 00:17:29.180
I can double check. but
that's about 150 properties.

245
00:17:29.348 --> 00:17:32.944
Rough terrain. 50
miles of rural farmland.

246
00:17:45.698 --> 00:17:47.428
You okay?

247
00:17:51.037 --> 00:17:52.767
You can't do it. can you?

248
00:18:00.379 --> 00:18:02.939
Jacob. Jacob. wait.

249
00:18:06.552 --> 00:18:09.420
Joey? I have lunch.

250
00:18:15.294 --> 00:18:16.387
Joey?

251
00:18:19.065 --> 00:18:20.727
Joey?

252
00:18:22.802 --> 00:18:24.896
Hey. where are you?

253
00:18:26.005 --> 00:18:27.735
Joey?

254
00:18:28.574 --> 00:18:29.735
Joey?

255
00:18:31.811 --> 00:18:34.280
Try and stop beating
yourself up. all right?

256
00:18:34.447 --> 00:18:35.608
Would you just stop it?

257
00:18:35.881 --> 00:18:37.440
I'm just trying to be a friend.

258
00:18:37.617 --> 00:18:40.781
- Really? With all this touchy-feely crap?
- Joey's gone.

259
00:19:03.976 --> 00:19:05.000
He's not in there.

260
00:19:05.177 --> 00:19:07.976
- You were supposed to talk to him.
- I did. he's scared.

261
00:19:08.914 --> 00:19:10.815
Gonna check the
woods. there's a trail.

262
00:19:10.983 --> 00:19:13.680
Yeah. let's split up.
We'll cover more ground.

263
00:19:29.035 --> 00:19:30.128
You all right?

264
00:19:31.971 --> 00:19:34.941
Yeah. me too. All right. bye.

265
00:19:36.876 --> 00:19:40.404
- Um. I'm gonna go out for a little while.
- Excuse me?

266
00:19:40.579 --> 00:19:42.673
I've been cooped up
in this house for days.

267
00:19:42.848 --> 00:19:44.714
I just want to meet
a friend for lunch.

268
00:19:44.884 --> 00:19:47.683
- I don't think that's a good idea.
- Regardless. I'm going.

269
00:19:48.387 --> 00:19:49.685
You can't keep me trapped.

270
00:19:50.389 --> 00:19:54.019
- I'll have to insist we accompany you.
- Whatever you have to do.

271
00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:10.886
Turner. TURNER:
<i>Joe Carroll's lawyer...</i>

272
00:20:10.910 --> 00:20:12.742
<i>just showed up to
see Ms. Matthews.</i>

273
00:20:12.912 --> 00:20:15.609
I don't know what they said.
but now she wants to leave.

274
00:20:15.781 --> 00:20:17.113
<i>Says she's going to lunch.</i>

275
00:20:17.283 --> 00:20:19.115
Go. Don't let her
out of your sight.

276
00:20:19.285 --> 00:20:20.583
I'm on it.

277
00:20:24.356 --> 00:20:25.847
Is it true?

278
00:20:26.025 --> 00:20:28.620
Joe Carroll has a
cult of serial killers?

279
00:20:28.794 --> 00:20:31.423
We don't know the
extent. but yeah.

280
00:20:32.398 --> 00:20:35.368
- Chief. you recognize this guy?
- Maybe.

281
00:20:35.534 --> 00:20:37.730
Ava. the missing girl
case in Rhinebeck...

282
00:20:37.903 --> 00:20:40.634
- could that be the guy...?
- I'll pull up the footage.

283
00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:45.041
A local girl. Megan Leeds. went
missing after her shift at a grocery store.

284
00:20:45.211 --> 00:20:47.476
We've got surveillance
footage from that night.

285
00:20:47.646 --> 00:20:50.582
Last time anyone saw
her. she was with this guy.

286
00:20:52.017 --> 00:20:54.145
- It's hard to see a face.
- Mm.

287
00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:55.783
May I?

288
00:20:57.056 --> 00:20:59.719
Just wanna route this
through the FBI server.

289
00:20:59.892 --> 00:21:01.554
- Advanced technology.
- Ha. ha. I bet.

290
00:21:11.670 --> 00:21:13.229
Hardy.

291
00:21:13.973 --> 00:21:15.168
Paul Torres.

292
00:21:16.742 --> 00:21:20.611
There's 20 farms matching the description
within a 25-mile radius of the store.

293
00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:23.340
- Most to the north. we should start there.
- Sounds like a plan.

294
00:21:23.482 --> 00:21:26.077
You and Weston start
there. I'll take Officer Lopez...

295
00:21:26.252 --> 00:21:28.414
hit the south.
cover more ground.

296
00:21:34.794 --> 00:21:35.853
Hon?

297
00:21:36.762 --> 00:21:40.290
Uh. this little man needs to
borrow the phone to call his mom.

298
00:21:43.636 --> 00:21:46.162
Are you Joey Matthews?

299
00:21:46.338 --> 00:21:49.274
Yeah. How do you know that?

300
00:21:51.277 --> 00:21:52.643
You were on the television.

301
00:21:52.812 --> 00:21:55.976
- The police are looking for you.
- They want to hurt me.

302
00:21:56.148 --> 00:21:59.778
Hurt you? The police? Who
would tell you such a thing?

303
00:21:59.952 --> 00:22:03.218
Joey? Joey!

304
00:22:03.389 --> 00:22:06.655
You scared me. I was
so worried about you.

305
00:22:08.627 --> 00:22:09.822
Come on. let's go home.

306
00:22:10.996 --> 00:22:12.692
I'm sorry. and you are?

307
00:22:12.865 --> 00:22:14.493
Denise. I'm Joey's nanny.

308
00:22:15.100 --> 00:22:18.161
I'm glad you found him. It's so
easy to get lost in these woods.

309
00:22:19.138 --> 00:22:22.666
The boy wanted to call his mother.
We were gonna let him use our phone.

310
00:22:22.842 --> 00:22:25.311
That's not necessary. We
have a phone at the house.

311
00:22:25.477 --> 00:22:27.571
- You can call your mom from there.
- I can?

312
00:22:27.746 --> 00:22:29.146
Of course. silly.

313
00:22:30.049 --> 00:22:32.814
Sorry to bother you. Come on.

314
00:22:36.922 --> 00:22:38.754
They said they saw me on TV.

315
00:22:38.991 --> 00:22:41.256
You shouldn't have run
off. I was worried sick.

316
00:22:41.427 --> 00:22:43.419
You said I could call my
mom. Did you mean it?

317
00:22:43.629 --> 00:22:45.825
Sure. You can call
her whenever you want.

318
00:22:46.565 --> 00:22:50.024
You found him. Where were
you? You had us worried.

319
00:22:50.202 --> 00:22:51.534
I didn't find him.

320
00:22:51.704 --> 00:22:54.230
Some friendly
neighbors back there did.

321
00:22:54.406 --> 00:22:56.432
They told Joey
they saw him on TV.

322
00:22:56.642 --> 00:22:59.339
They did. huh? Huh.

323
00:22:59.511 --> 00:23:03.573
Shoot. I forgot to thank
them for helping out.

324
00:23:03.749 --> 00:23:05.513
Do you mind?

325
00:23:06.218 --> 00:23:08.084
Sure. I'm great at thank yous.

326
00:23:08.587 --> 00:23:09.714
Come on. let's go.

327
00:23:12.524 --> 00:23:14.924
- It was that boy from the news.
- Tell them to hurry. Clark.

328
00:23:18.964 --> 00:23:20.296
I wouldn't do that.

329
00:23:28.474 --> 00:23:31.273
We've covered about 40
square miles of the county.

330
00:23:31.443 --> 00:23:34.563
Looks like four more farms in the area.
- <i>Officer Lopez. this is dispatch.</i>

331
00:23:35.281 --> 00:23:36.442
This is Lopez. Go ahead.

332
00:23:36.615 --> 00:23:39.107
<i>Just got a call from that
Sullivan house on Route 9.</i>

333
00:23:39.285 --> 00:23:41.413
<i>They saw that boy
everyone's looking for.</i>

334
00:23:42.054 --> 00:23:44.148
- How fast can you get there?
- It's a couple miles.

335
00:23:44.323 --> 00:23:46.724
Dispatch. we're en route now.

336
00:23:54.900 --> 00:23:57.631
- Can I dial?
- Eager beaver.

337
00:23:57.970 --> 00:24:00.201
- You wanna call her now?
- You said I could.

338
00:24:00.940 --> 00:24:03.637
I'll get the phone. You're
not going anywhere. right?

339
00:24:03.809 --> 00:24:05.641
I promise.

340
00:24:32.037 --> 00:24:33.266
Jacob?

341
00:24:34.873 --> 00:24:36.637
Paul?

342
00:24:51.290 --> 00:24:53.384
- Who are you?
- Roderick sent me.

343
00:24:53.559 --> 00:24:56.495
We need to go. Now.

344
00:25:08.173 --> 00:25:09.539
- Lisa.
- Hey.

345
00:25:09.708 --> 00:25:12.200
- Thank you so much for meeting me.
- Of course.

346
00:25:14.646 --> 00:25:17.582
I've been so worried about you.

347
00:25:18.984 --> 00:25:22.819
Oh. yeah. just ignore the
FBI men. They insisted.

348
00:25:22.988 --> 00:25:24.012
Oh.

349
00:25:24.723 --> 00:25:28.592
Everyone should have an
entourage. It's so good to see you.

350
00:25:28.794 --> 00:25:32.663
- I called and I left some messages...
- It's just been such a nightmare.

351
00:25:35.968 --> 00:25:37.994
Um. let's order.

352
00:25:38.170 --> 00:25:39.695
- Order.
- Okay.

353
00:25:46.178 --> 00:25:47.544
Anybody here?

354
00:25:47.713 --> 00:25:50.182
Not sure. They're not
answering their phone.

355
00:25:54.119 --> 00:25:55.382
Police department!

356
00:25:58.557 --> 00:26:00.355
Let me check the back.

357
00:26:23.882 --> 00:26:25.441
Clark?

358
00:26:26.552 --> 00:26:29.420
Nora? Anyone home?

359
00:26:50.375 --> 00:26:51.638
Oh. my God.

360
00:26:56.281 --> 00:26:57.806
Call it in.

361
00:27:02.387 --> 00:27:03.821
Hey.

362
00:27:04.089 --> 00:27:06.752
It's okay. Call it in.

363
00:27:13.031 --> 00:27:16.866
Dispatch. this is Officer
Lopez. MAN <i>Dispatch. go ahead.</i>

364
00:27:17.035 --> 00:27:18.970
They were just here.

365
00:27:19.705 --> 00:27:21.435
- We have a 10-55...
- Follow me.

366
00:27:21.607 --> 00:27:23.337
At the Sullivan house.

367
00:27:38.657 --> 00:27:39.818
They're on foot.

368
00:27:41.126 --> 00:27:42.617
How close is the next farm?

369
00:27:42.995 --> 00:27:44.827
About a half-mile
through those woods.

370
00:28:11.056 --> 00:28:14.857
- That's it. White house. black shutters.
- You sure?

371
00:28:23.635 --> 00:28:28.300
We're at the farmhouse. about a
half a mile west of the Sullivan house.

372
00:28:28.473 --> 00:28:30.567
- Pursuing suspects.
- That's them.

373
00:28:42.187 --> 00:28:43.416
Hey. where are you?

374
00:28:43.589 --> 00:28:47.253
About a half a mile west of the
house where we found the dead couple.

375
00:28:47.459 --> 00:28:52.090
I've ID'd Jacob Wells. Paul Torres.
We're gonna need some backup here.

376
00:28:52.264 --> 00:28:54.927
Consider it done. Wait for it.

377
00:28:55.100 --> 00:28:58.537
We're gonna get
closer and stabilize.

378
00:28:58.704 --> 00:29:01.173
You notify me when you're here.

379
00:29:02.541 --> 00:29:04.601
Hey. You up for this?

380
00:29:05.477 --> 00:29:07.070
Yeah.

381
00:29:07.279 --> 00:29:10.044
All right. We're gonna
get closer to the house.

382
00:29:10.215 --> 00:29:12.047
Try to get a better look. Okay?

383
00:29:12.217 --> 00:29:13.583
Okay.

384
00:29:16.288 --> 00:29:19.554
Emma. whose car
is that out there?

385
00:29:21.793 --> 00:29:24.922
Jacob. Paul. this is
Hank. Roderick sent him.

386
00:29:25.097 --> 00:29:27.760
We need to get out of here.
guys. You have 10 minutes.

387
00:29:27.933 --> 00:29:30.596
Pack light. I don't
have a lot of room.

388
00:29:32.437 --> 00:29:34.406
So Roderick came through.

389
00:29:34.773 --> 00:29:36.765
- Where's Joey?
- In his bedroom.

390
00:29:36.942 --> 00:29:39.002
Let's get packed
up. I'll get him last.

391
00:29:42.080 --> 00:29:45.642
Do these three have any connection
to Dutchess County? Any family?

392
00:29:45.817 --> 00:29:48.753
I just heard from Agent Weston.
They found the farmhouse.

393
00:29:51.256 --> 00:29:53.816
I want every available
agent. SWAT and tactical.

394
00:29:54.026 --> 00:29:56.757
Alert ATF. set up mobile
command at the area.

395
00:29:56.928 --> 00:29:58.328
Notify air transport.

396
00:29:58.530 --> 00:30:02.262
Then call the Albany and New Haven field
offices and pull men from Poughkeepsie.

397
00:30:02.434 --> 00:30:04.154
Tell them I'm on my way.
- Got it.

398
00:30:04.269 --> 00:30:06.295
I'm so happy we did this.
- Me too.

399
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:09.407
It's really good to
get out of the house.

400
00:30:10.809 --> 00:30:13.938
Um. why don't you order
me a double espresso?

401
00:30:14.112 --> 00:30:16.547
I'm gonna be right back.

402
00:30:20.552 --> 00:30:22.748
Just going to the
little girl's room.

403
00:30:27.326 --> 00:30:29.318
No. I'll go.

404
00:31:27.018 --> 00:31:29.317
I'm gonna go around back
and see what I can see.

405
00:31:30.222 --> 00:31:33.386
I'll get to the barn. Better sight
line to the front of the house.

406
00:31:33.558 --> 00:31:35.186
I'll meet you there.

407
00:31:36.561 --> 00:31:37.620
Eyes up.

408
00:31:55.714 --> 00:31:58.013
<i>It's me. Do you have the mother?</i>

409
00:31:58.183 --> 00:31:59.742
She's late.

410
00:32:05.257 --> 00:32:08.193
Give her more time. I'll call
you as soon as I'm on the road.

411
00:32:58.944 --> 00:33:00.572
Mr. Hardy?

412
00:33:09.921 --> 00:33:11.480
Stop.

413
00:33:12.457 --> 00:33:16.019
- Put your hands where I can see them.
- Is something wrong. officer?

414
00:33:16.628 --> 00:33:19.097
- Who are you?
- What's going on. officer?

415
00:33:19.264 --> 00:33:21.790
- I said raise your hands up.
- Look...

416
00:33:21.967 --> 00:33:24.027
- Don't come any closer.
- I'm sorry. officer.

417
00:33:24.236 --> 00:33:26.728
I'm just a little nervous
with that gun in my face.

418
00:33:27.138 --> 00:33:30.472
- Stop it!
- I am sorry. officer...

419
00:33:30.642 --> 00:33:33.077
Keep your hands up! I need
you to keep your hands up!

420
00:33:54.366 --> 00:33:55.629
Don't move!

421
00:34:12.217 --> 00:34:13.708
Did you guys hear that?

422
00:34:19.457 --> 00:34:22.552
Where'd he go? EMMA: Hank?

423
00:34:22.727 --> 00:34:25.390
Oh. man. this is not good.

424
00:34:32.337 --> 00:34:36.274
He can't be far. Look
around. We'll find him.

425
00:34:38.977 --> 00:34:40.417
- I'm good.
- No. listen to me.

426
00:34:40.779 --> 00:34:43.146
Easy. Stay on the ground.

427
00:34:43.348 --> 00:34:46.978
All available units.
Officer down. Officer down.

428
00:34:47.152 --> 00:34:49.280
Farmhouse just west of Route 9.

429
00:34:50.722 --> 00:34:53.715
We need to knock them off
one by one. it's our best option.

430
00:34:53.892 --> 00:34:56.657
No. no. no. Wait.
wait. Listen to me.

431
00:34:58.063 --> 00:35:01.795
I need to you take this. I need
you to hold it right here. okay?

432
00:35:02.367 --> 00:35:04.734
Right there. Help
is on the way. okay?

433
00:35:05.270 --> 00:35:08.934
Help is coming. just hold on.

434
00:35:09.107 --> 00:35:11.576
Hold on. hold on.

435
00:35:12.010 --> 00:35:13.945
Hold on. hold on. hol...

436
00:35:19.284 --> 00:35:20.912
<i>Ryan?</i>

437
00:35:21.953 --> 00:35:25.446
<i>Ryan? Hey. Ryan?</i>

438
00:35:25.824 --> 00:35:27.656
It's too late.

439
00:35:28.193 --> 00:35:30.162
He's gone.

440
00:35:34.432 --> 00:35:35.525
Damn it.

441
00:35:37.669 --> 00:35:40.901
All right. hang tight.
We're a few minutes out.

442
00:35:43.942 --> 00:35:45.103
I'm going in.

443
00:36:06.164 --> 00:36:07.792
Hey!

444
00:36:10.168 --> 00:36:12.069
Open the door!

445
00:36:14.039 --> 00:36:17.237
Let me out! Open the door!

446
00:36:27.318 --> 00:36:29.549
- You asked for an update.
- Mm-hm.

447
00:36:29.721 --> 00:36:32.691
The FBI located the farmhouse
where they're holding your son.

448
00:36:32.857 --> 00:36:35.326
- Do they have him?
- No. not yet.

449
00:36:36.094 --> 00:36:39.189
I've also delivered your
message to the press.

450
00:36:39.364 --> 00:36:42.061
And? How did it go?

451
00:36:42.233 --> 00:36:44.532
Besides my appearing
like a raving mad woman...

452
00:36:44.703 --> 00:36:47.867
it was heard by everyone. Local
and national news picked it up.

453
00:36:48.039 --> 00:36:50.008
My story has caused
quite the sensation?

454
00:36:50.175 --> 00:36:53.407
The FBI has done a good job at
minimizing the details but yes...

455
00:36:53.578 --> 00:36:56.878
the press has been considerable.

456
00:36:59.250 --> 00:37:01.014
And Claire?

457
00:37:02.120 --> 00:37:05.887
I delivered the message to her
as well. I haven't heard anything.

458
00:37:06.057 --> 00:37:08.925
Well. when you do. I'll
need another update.

459
00:37:10.028 --> 00:37:14.056
You have been very
helpful today. Thank you.

460
00:37:14.699 --> 00:37:16.497
What have I done. Joe?

461
00:37:18.069 --> 00:37:22.769
The poem I read. I triggered something.
You sent a message to someone.

462
00:37:22.941 --> 00:37:24.204
What am I a part of?

463
00:37:24.375 --> 00:37:26.571
I'm surprised at you. Olivia.

464
00:37:26.878 --> 00:37:30.781
I chose you precisely for your
ambition and lack of conscience.

465
00:37:30.949 --> 00:37:32.542
I won't be your messenger.

466
00:37:32.717 --> 00:37:35.243
The role of the messenger
is somewhat preferable...

467
00:37:35.420 --> 00:37:36.786
to that of recipient.

468
00:37:39.290 --> 00:37:41.418
I'm sure you'd agree.

469
00:37:46.297 --> 00:37:50.598
You must be Hank
Flynn. Please. come in.

470
00:37:56.441 --> 00:37:59.411
- Thank you for seeing me after hours.
- Of course.

471
00:38:00.311 --> 00:38:01.540
What can I do for you?

472
00:38:02.814 --> 00:38:06.148
- Joe Carroll asked me to see you.
- Excuse me?

473
00:38:06.818 --> 00:38:10.414
- About what?
- He wanted me to give you a message.

474
00:38:17.162 --> 00:38:19.290
Please...

475
00:38:20.431 --> 00:38:22.457
do not bring me
into this any further.

476
00:38:22.634 --> 00:38:24.967
We're just getting started.

477
00:38:25.136 --> 00:38:28.470
I have so much more
work for you to do.

478
00:38:28.640 --> 00:38:32.133
Did you bring pen and paper?
You're going to need to write this down.

479
00:38:33.678 --> 00:38:36.204
Snap. snap. Miss Warren.

480
00:38:45.056 --> 00:38:46.080
Hmm.

481
00:39:16.154 --> 00:39:18.749
- Get in.
- And go where?

482
00:39:18.923 --> 00:39:23.054
If you want to see Joey. get
in now. I won't say it again.

483
00:39:59.530 --> 00:40:00.930
Damn it.

484
00:40:04.435 --> 00:40:06.301
He's dead.

485
00:40:06.938 --> 00:40:10.670
Local cop. Think he's alone?

486
00:40:55.320 --> 00:40:58.484
- Megan? Shh. Shh.
- Aah!

487
00:40:58.656 --> 00:41:01.854
I'm Ryan Hardy with the FBI.
I'm gonna get you out of here.

488
00:41:02.026 --> 00:41:05.929
But I need you
to be quiet. okay?

489
00:41:10.335 --> 00:41:11.428
How many are up there?

490
00:41:11.602 --> 00:41:14.333
I've seen three.
They're gonna kill me.

491
00:41:26.851 --> 00:41:29.051
They're crazy. You have to
get me out of here right now.

492
00:41:29.220 --> 00:41:30.244
Shh. Shh. Shh.

493
00:41:32.056 --> 00:41:33.217
Is there a boy upstairs?

494
00:41:33.391 --> 00:41:35.019
I don't know. Get
me out of here.

495
00:41:38.296 --> 00:41:43.234
I will be right
back. I promise you.

496
00:42:30.848 --> 00:42:33.943
Hey. Joey. Remember me?

497
00:42:36.220 --> 00:42:38.553
I'm a friend of your mom's.

498
00:42:38.723 --> 00:42:40.123
She sent me to come take you.

499
00:42:43.161 --> 00:42:46.325
Do not move.
